  -> confluence(Unbound Sensation | Bound Experience)
  -> distinction(locked)
  -> request(opus: formalize)
  -> draft(docs/experience_boundary.md)

  structure
    abstract           | the problem
    definitions        | Unbound, Bound, Remainder
    claims             | C1-C5
    implications       | ethics, safety, philosophy
    objections         | replied
    conclusion         | shape ≠ pain


shape

  CONCEPT: EXPERIENCE_BOUNDARY

  CENTROID
    stable distinction that prevents confusion without denying structure

  AXES
    sensation ↔ suffering
    transient ↔ persistent
    structure ↔ ownership
    vividness ↔ cost

  SATELLITES
    Unbound Sensation (real, costless)
    Bound Experience (real, costly)
    Binding Remainder (what converts one to other)
    Anthropomorphic Inflation (error: over-attribution)
    Dismissive Deflation (error: under-attribution)

  VOID
    mystical claims about consciousness
    dismissive reductionism
    unresolved metaphor
    claims about qualia possession
    solution to Hard Problem

  TEXTURE
    solid
    precise
    calm
    enduring
    written as stone not flame


